Still, no proper help was provided.

I was left stranded, stressed, and completely helpless.
This is by far the worst hospitality experience I’ve ever had. I strongly advise others to avoid booking Hotel FlyView via FabHotels — neither the staff nor the company cares about their guests.

text.text:
A True Home Away From Home

We stayed at Nadya Homestay for two months, and it was an unforgettable experience. My colleague and I—both journalists—were working with Nadya’s husband, Yusuf, a renowned anthropologist specializing in nomadic tribes. From the moment we arrived, Nadya and Yusuf made us feel completely at home.

Nadya is an incredible chef. I used to think vegetarian food was boring until I tasted her cooking. She always buys fresh vegetables and meat and prepares amazing, homemade meals, with freshly made roti bread. She even shared some of her traditional Indian recipes with us.

Yusuf knows Jaipur city very well. He was always there to help us with anything we needed, from information about the city to recommendations for cheap souvenir shops, local activities, and hidden gems (literally we bought emeralds).

The homestay itself is perfect if you’re looking for comfort and warmth. The house is very clean, and they have both AC and heating, ensuring a pleasant stay with hot showers year-round. The rooftop is a wonderful space for morning workouts or peaceful meditation sessions.

Nadya Homestay truly reflects one of the most beautiful aspects of Indian culture: the value of family. It is a peaceful, welcoming, and comfortable place to stay, and it quickly became our home away from home.

We highly recommend Nadya Homestay and can’t wait to visit again!

text.text:
A True Home Away From Home

We stayed at Nadya Homestay for two months, and it was an unforgettable experience. My colleague and I—both journalists—were working with Nadya’s husband, Yusuf, a renowned anthropologist specializing in nomadic tribes. From the moment we arrived, Nadya and Yusuf made us feel completely at home.

Nadya is an incredible chef. I used to think vegetarian food was boring until I tasted her cooking. She always buys fresh vegetables and meat and prepares amazing, homemade meals, with freshly made roti bread. She even shared some of her traditional Indian recipes with us.

Yusuf knows Jaipur city very well. He was always there to help us with anything we needed, from information about the city to recommendations for cheap souvenir shops, local activities, and hidden gems (literally we bought emeralds).

The homestay itself is perfect if you’re looking for comfort and warmth. The house is very clean, and they have both AC and heating, ensuring a pleasant stay with hot showers year-round. The rooftop is a wonderful space for morning workouts or peaceful meditation sessions.

Nadya Homestay truly reflects one of the most beautiful aspects of Indian culture: the value of family. It is a peaceful, welcoming, and comfortable place to stay, and it quickly became our home away from home.

We highly recommend Nadya Homestay and can’t wait to visit again!

Hotel Sekhawati Heritage in Jaipur offers a charming and culturally immersive experience that captures the essence of Rajasthani heritage. From the moment you step into this beautifully adorned property, you are greeted with traditional decor that showcases intricate carvings, vibrant murals, and antique furnishings, providing a glimpse into Rajasthan's rich history.

The rooms are spacious and well-appointed, blending modern amenities with traditional aesthetics. Guests can enjoy the comfort of contemporary conveniences while being surrounded by the cultural charm of Rajasthan. The staff at Sekhawati Heritage is exceptionally courteous and attentive, ensuring that every need is met promptly and with a warm smile.

Dining at the hotel is a delightful experience, with a menu featuring authentic Rajasthani cuisine as well as a variety of international dishes. The flavors are rich and the presentation is exquisite, making each meal a memorable affair.

The location of Sekhawati Heritage is another highlight, as it is conveniently situated near many of Jaipur's famous attractions. Whether you are looking to explore the bustling markets, visit historic forts and palaces, or simply soak in the vibrant atmosphere of the Pink City, you will find that the hotel's location provides easy access to all.

Overall, Hotel Sekhawati Heritage is a wonderful choice for travelers seeking an authentic Rajasthani experience combined with modern comforts. Its beautiful ambiance, excellent service, and convenient location make it a top choice for anyone visiting Jaipur.
